                android:text="Prepare Lumpia Filling:

In a large pan or wok, sauté garlic and onions in cooking oil until fragrant.
Add ground pork (or pork and beef mixture) and cook until browned.
Add soy sauce, salt, and pepper. Stir in carrots, green beans, cabbage, and bean sprouts. Cook until the vegetables are tender yet still crisp. Adjust the seasoning according to your taste.
Prepare Lumpia Wrapper:

Separate lumpia wrappers carefully. Cover them with a damp cloth to prevent drying while assembling.
Assemble Lumpia:

Take a lumpia wrapper and place it on a clean surface. Spoon about 2-3 tablespoons of the filling along one edge of the wrapper.
Fold the sides of the wrapper towards the center, then roll the lumpia tightly, sealing the edge with the cornstarch-water paste.
Repeat:

Repeat the process until all the filling is used.
Heat Oil for Frying:

In a deep pan, heat cooking oil for deep frying to around 350°F (175°C).
Fry Lumpia:

Carefully place the lumpia in the hot oil, a few at a time, making sure not to overcrowd the pan. Fry until golden brown and crispy, turning occasionally to ensure even cooking.
Drain and Serve:

Remove the fried lumpia using a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Serve with Sauce:

Serve the lumpia hot with a dipping sauce made of vinegar, soy sauce, minced garlic, and pepper"
